## For agents
Read [`AGENTS.md`](AGENTS.md) first. It is the canonical rules file (multi-vendor: Claude, Codex, Cursor, Aider, Gemini CLI all consume it). Claude-specific mechanics live in [`CLAUDE.md`](CLAUDE.md). The harness (skills, hooks, settings) lives under [`.claude/`](.claude/); the [`.claude/README.md`](.claude/README.md) explains the layout.
## Status
**Phase A — Foundations and audience (June-July 2026).** Pre-alpha. Private. No public release.
The keystone app is **Buddhi**, the private personal-context assistant, built on the Akshi substrate (two-brand: Akshi = substrate/platform, Buddhi = the consumer app). See [`docs/Decisions.md`](docs/Decisions.md) D-73.
Two predecessor systems (a Rust agent substrate "akshi-v2", a Dart/Flutter learning product "Kalvi") were retired in June 2026; their validated designs carry forward, no code is ported. See [`docs/Decisions.md`](docs/Decisions.md) D-1 and [`docs/Specification.md`](docs/Specification.md) §14.
